&reftitle.setup;




 &reftitle.required;


  In order to use the OpenSSL functions you need to install the OpenSSL library.
  PHP 7 requires at least OpenSSL >= 0.9.8. Other versions
  (PHP >= 7.1.0) require OpenSSL >= 1.0.1. Only PHP >= 8.1 supports
  OpenSSL >= 3.0.




   You are strongly encouraged to use a maintained OpenSSL version,
   otherwise your web server could be vulnerable to attack.






&reference.openssl.configure;



&reference.openssl.ini;





 &reftitle.resources;


  Prior to PHP 8.0.0, there were 3 resource types defined in the OpenSSL module:

   OpenSSL key
   OpenSSL X.509
   OpenSSL X.509 CSR
